WEBVTT

00:02.673 --> 00:03.704
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

00:03.704 --> 00:05.676
MAX, TIME FOR BREAKFAST.

00:05.676 --> 00:07.508
WHAT HAPPENED IN HERE?

00:07.508 --> 00:09.540
WHAT DID YOU DO
TO YOUR PILLOW?

00:09.540 --> 00:13.184
IT KEPT ME FROM SLEEPING,
SO I PUNCHED IT.

00:13.184 --> 00:15.546
AND THEN I HIT IT
WITH MY BAT,

00:15.546 --> 00:19.420
AND I RIPPED IT APART
WITH MY TEETH.

00:19.420 --> 00:21.422
OKAY. THAT´S...

00:21.422 --> 00:24.155
PERFECTLY NORMAL, SON.

00:24.155 --> 00:27.298
ANGIE, YOU WANT TO GET IN HERE
AND BRING A CRUCIFIX?!

00:31.062 --> 00:33.404
MAX!

00:33.404 --> 00:34.565
WHY DID YOU DO THIS?

00:34.565 --> 00:36.467
I CAN´T SLEEP.

00:36.467 --> 00:38.709
I HAVEN´T BEEN
ABLE TO FOR A WEEK.

00:38.709 --> 00:41.041
WHY DIDN´T YOU TELL US?

00:41.041 --> 00:43.544
WELL, I ALREADY HAVE
DYSLEXIA AND DYSCALCULIA.

00:43.544 --> 00:45.346
THE LAST THING
I NEED TO FIND OUT

00:45.346 --> 00:49.320
IS THAT I HAVE
DYSSLEEPIA.

00:49.320 --> 00:51.422
IT´S CALLED "INSOMNIA."

00:51.422 --> 00:53.454
I KNEW THERE´D
BE A WORD FOR IT.

00:53.454 --> 00:56.627
THERE´S A WORD FOR EVERYTHING
THAT´S WRONG WITH ME!

00:56.627 --> 01:00.331
HONEY, THERE´S NOTHING
WRONG WITH YOU.

01:00.331 --> 01:02.733
I´M IN SPECIAL ED,

01:02.733 --> 01:05.196
I STUDY THREE TIMES HARDER
THAN ANYONE ELSE,

01:05.196 --> 01:07.398
AND I STILL MIGHT
FLUNK THE 5th GRADE.

01:07.398 --> 01:09.340
OH, YEAH, I´M A WINNER.

01:11.542 --> 01:14.345
LOOK, YOU´RE UNDER
A LOT OF PRESSURE.

01:14.345 --> 01:17.208
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE TAKE
THE DAY OFF FROM SCHOOL

01:17.208 --> 01:20.251
AND I BRING YOUR BREAKFAST
UP HERE, HMM?

01:20.251 --> 01:21.512
THANKS.

01:21.512 --> 01:23.854
GOOD.
OKAY, NOW, YOU REST.

01:23.854 --> 01:25.786
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,
YOU´LL FALL ASLEEP,

01:25.786 --> 01:28.219
AND EVERYTHING
WILL BE ALL RIGHT.

01:31.492 --> 01:34.495
BE GONE!

01:34.495 --> 01:38.169
NIGHTY-NIGHT.

01:38.169 --> 01:41.772
AN 11-YEAR-OLD SHOULD
NOT BE AWAKE ALL NIGHT.

01:41.772 --> 01:44.375
UGH -- BE GONE!

01:46.477 --> 01:47.778
AND STAYING
AWAKE ALL NIGHT´S

01:47.778 --> 01:49.710
NOT GONNA HELP HIM
PASS THE 5th GRADE.

01:49.710 --> 01:51.342
HEY, DADDY.

01:51.342 --> 01:52.843
HI, ANGIE, MY ANGEL.

01:52.843 --> 01:55.246
HELLO, BENITA,
MY LITTLE DEVIL.

01:56.517 --> 01:58.789
HELLO, GEORGE, MY --

01:58.789 --> 02:01.792
YEAH, THERE YOU ARE.

02:01.792 --> 02:04.355
HEY, VIC, YOU KNOW,
THEY SELL BACON IN THE STORES,

02:04.355 --> 02:08.199
AND, WOW, YOU CAN EVEN COOK IT
AT YOUR OWN HOUSE.

02:08.199 --> 02:10.401
GEORGE, MAYBE HE NEEDS
A PSYCHOLOGIST.

02:10.401 --> 02:13.264
HE´S NOT CRAZY, ANGIE,
HE´S JUST OLD AND LONELY,

02:13.264 --> 02:15.866
AND TOO CHEAP
TO BUY HIS OWN BREAKFAST.

02:15.866 --> 02:18.369
I´M TALKING ABOUT MAX.

02:18.369 --> 02:19.770
WHAT´S WRONG WITH MAX?

02:19.770 --> 02:21.642
DADDY, HE´S SO STRESSED OUT
ABOUT SCHOOL,

02:21.642 --> 02:23.414
HE RIPPED UP
HIS PILLOW LAST NIGHT.

02:23.414 --> 02:25.876
DOES YOUR HOSPITAL HAVE
ANY GOOD CHILD PSYCHOLOGISTS?

02:25.876 --> 02:28.419
PSYCHOLOGISTS?
NO WAY.

02:28.419 --> 02:29.720
LOOK, ANGIE,
WE´RE LOPEZES,

02:29.720 --> 02:31.552
AND WE DON´T GO FOR HELP

02:31.552 --> 02:32.883
UNTIL RIGHT BEFORE
IT´S TOO LATE.

02:32.883 --> 02:36.257
DADDY, YOU´RE A DOCTOR.
HELP ME OUT HERE.

02:36.257 --> 02:37.758
THERAPY´S FOR THE WEAK.

02:37.758 --> 02:39.490
CASTRO STOLE MY ISLAND,

02:39.490 --> 02:42.533
AND A WEB DESIGNER
STOLE MY WIFE.

02:42.533 --> 02:44.335
BUT DO YOU SEE ME
CRYING LIKE A BABY

02:44.335 --> 02:46.467
TO SOMEONE WHO THINKS
THAT SMOKING A CIGAR

02:46.467 --> 02:49.340
IS A SIGN OF LATENT
HOMOSEXUALITY?

02:49.340 --> 02:51.772
SOMETIMES A CIGAR
IS JUST A CIGAR --

02:51.772 --> 02:54.245
UNLESS IT´S A DOMINICAN
OR A HONDURAN.

02:54.245 --> 02:57.248
THOSE ARE SPECIFICALLY GROWN
FOR HOMOSEXUALS.

02:58.909 --> 03:01.952
FINALLY,
THE VOICE OF REASON.

03:01.952 --> 03:04.655
OKAY, IF YOU
DON´T LIKE THERAPY,

03:04.655 --> 03:06.717
THERE ARE OTHER WAYS
TO DEAL WITH STRESS.

03:06.717 --> 03:08.559
MAYBE IF MAX COULD
DO SOMETHING CREATIVE,

03:08.559 --> 03:10.491
IT COULD TAKE HIS MIND
OFF HIS PROBLEMS

03:10.491 --> 03:11.792
AND HELP HIM SLEEP.

03:11.792 --> 03:13.594
WHAT ABOUT AN ART CLASS?

03:13.594 --> 03:15.866
WHAT?
HOW IS ART GONNA HELP HIM

03:15.866 --> 03:17.798
GET RID
OF HIS FRUSTRATIONS?

03:17.798 --> 03:20.371
[ French accent ]
OH, I AM SO ANGRY.

03:20.371 --> 03:22.633
I WILL PAINT A LIVELY
FRENCH CAFE SCENE.

03:22.633 --> 03:25.936
AH HA HA HA!

03:25.936 --> 03:28.509
OKAY, LOOK,
I´M GONNA TAKE HIS BREAKFAST UP.

03:28.509 --> 03:30.611
WE CAN FIGURE
THIS OUT LATER.

03:32.343 --> 03:35.686
I´LL TELL YOU
HOW I GET RID OF MY STRESS.

03:35.686 --> 03:37.688
I BURN IT OFF
AT THE GYM,

03:37.688 --> 03:39.950
AND THEN
I GET A SPRAY TAN.

03:39.950 --> 03:44.695
DOESN´T HURT MY SKIN,
AND I LOOK FANTASTIC.

03:44.695 --> 03:48.459
SO YOU´RE ORANGE
DOWNSTAIRS, TOO?

03:48.459 --> 03:50.431
MOM!

03:51.432 --> 03:53.564
OYE, CHICO,

03:53.564 --> 03:56.006
I GOT IT --
BOXING.

03:56.006 --> 03:57.668
BOXING?

03:57.668 --> 03:59.570
WHEN I WAS A BOY
IN CUBA,

03:59.570 --> 04:00.971
I SUFFERED
FROM THE ANXIETY,

04:00.971 --> 04:02.973
SO MY FATHER
TAUGHT ME HOW TO BOX.

04:02.973 --> 04:05.916
I FORGOT ABOUT MY PROBLEMS,
AND I GOT STRONGER.

04:05.916 --> 04:08.979
I COULD FACE ANY OPPONENT
ON THE ISLAND WITHOUT FEAR.

04:08.979 --> 04:10.621
YEAH,
THEN CASTRO SHOWED UP,

04:10.621 --> 04:12.453
YOU HID YOUR WATCH
IN YOUR BUTT,

04:12.453 --> 04:14.625
AND YOU PADDLED TO MIAMI.

04:14.625 --> 04:17.588
YES, BUT I WAS
SO TOUGH FROM BOXING,

04:17.588 --> 04:20.361
NO MAN DARED
TAKE THAT WATCH FROM ME.

04:21.832 --> 04:24.465
OOH, VIC,
YOUR SHOE´S UNTIED.

04:24.465 --> 04:26.297
OH, YEAH?

04:26.297 --> 04:28.469
LOOK AT THAT.
I´M LATE FOR WORK.

04:30.641 --> 04:32.042
LOOK, VIC,

04:32.042 --> 04:33.744
BOXING IS A GOOD WAY
TO BLOW OFF STEAM,

04:33.744 --> 04:35.346
BUT ANGIE WOULD
NEVER GO FOR IT.

04:35.346 --> 04:37.608
SHE´D BE TOO WORRIED
THAT MAX IS GONNA GET HURT.

04:37.608 --> 04:39.310
HOW CAN HE GET HURT,
GEORGE?

04:39.310 --> 04:41.752
HE´S HALF MEXICAN
AND HALF CUBAN.

04:41.752 --> 04:43.984
HE WAS BORN TO FIGHT!

04:43.984 --> 04:47.358
AND LIVE AT HOME
UNTIL HE´S 40.

04:47.358 --> 04:50.421
LISTEN, ANGIE DOESN´T
HAVE TO KNOW ABOUT THIS

04:50.421 --> 04:53.424
UNTIL WE SEE IF MAX
LIKES BOXING OR NOT, HMM?

04:53.424 --> 04:54.725
IN THE MEANTIME,

04:54.725 --> 04:56.897
WE´LL SAY HE´S
TAKING ART CLASSES.

04:56.897 --> 04:58.929
NO. LOOK,
I PROMISED ANGIE

04:58.929 --> 05:01.372
I WASN´T GONNA GO
BEHIND HER BACK ANYMORE.

05:01.372 --> 05:03.033
I CAN´T LIE TO HER.

05:03.033 --> 05:07.638
WHAT IF I LIE
AND YOU NOD VIGOROUSLY?

05:07.638 --> 05:10.481
I CAN DO THAT.

05:10.481 --> 05:13.384
NOW I´M REALLY WORRIED --
MAX WANTS TO KNOW

05:13.384 --> 05:17.648
IF WE HAVE ANY PILLOWCASES
THAT TASTE BETTER.

05:17.648 --> 05:19.650
ANGIE,
I´VE MADE A DECISION.

05:19.650 --> 05:20.991
TELL HER, VIC.

05:20.991 --> 05:24.655
MAX IS TAKING
ART CLASSES.

05:24.655 --> 05:26.997
REALLY?

05:26.997 --> 05:28.629
ALL RIGHT.

05:28.629 --> 05:32.703
FOR ONCE YOU´RE ADMITTING
I HAD A GOOD IDEA.

05:32.703 --> 05:34.835
ADMIT IT, GEORGE.

05:40.911 --> 05:43.514
[ INTRO TO WAR´S
"LOW RIDER" PLAYS ]

05:54.385 --> 05:59.830
♫ ALL MY FRIENDS
KNOW THE LOW RIDER ♫

06:31.121 --> 06:33.924
COME ON, MAX!
THROW SOME COMBINATIONS, HUH?

06:33.924 --> 06:35.726
HEY,
HOW´S OUR BOY DOING?

06:35.726 --> 06:38.429
HE´S HAVING A GREAT TIME,
AND HE´S SLEEPING LIKE A BABY.

06:38.429 --> 06:40.100
WOW, LOOK AT HIM GO.

06:40.100 --> 06:41.902
TWO WEEKS IN THE GYM

06:41.902 --> 06:45.676
AND MY GRANDSON
IS ALREADY A KILLER.

06:45.676 --> 06:48.108
WELL, I GUESS TOUGHNESS
SKIPS A GENERATION,

06:48.108 --> 06:50.410
HUH, PRINCESS?

06:51.642 --> 06:53.514
I COULD HAVE BEEN
A GOOD BOXER.

06:53.514 --> 06:55.716
YOU JUST NEVER ENCOURAGED ME,
OR FED ME.

06:55.716 --> 06:57.417
THAT´S NOT TRUE.

06:57.417 --> 06:59.590
WHO GETS STRONG
ON POWDERED MILK?

07:03.854 --> 07:05.526
LOOKING GOOD, KID.

07:05.526 --> 07:07.528
YOU MIGHT WANT
TO KEEP YOUR CHIN DOWN.

07:07.528 --> 07:11.462
SORRY, I DON´T TAKE
BOXING ADVICE FROM GIRLS.

07:11.462 --> 07:13.664
WELL, LISTEN,
IF YOU´RE GONNA TRAIN IN MY GYM,

07:13.664 --> 07:15.836
YOU´RE GONNA
HAVE TO LISTEN TO ME.

07:15.836 --> 07:17.808
MAX, THIS IS LAILA ALI.

07:17.808 --> 07:20.571
[ Imitating Muhammad Ali ]
THIS IS MUHAMMAD ALI´S DAUGHTER.

07:20.571 --> 07:23.514
SHE´S THE GREATEST FEMALE
FIGHTER OF ALL TIMES, MAN,

07:23.514 --> 07:26.617
AND SHE´S SO PRETTY.

07:26.617 --> 07:28.819
YEAH?
WELL, CAN YOU DO THIS?

07:28.819 --> 07:30.781
WATCH OUT.

07:32.783 --> 07:34.124
LET ME TRY.

07:34.124 --> 07:36.226
NO, HE BELIEVES YOU.

07:45.836 --> 07:47.768
IS IT OVER?!

07:49.840 --> 07:52.202
YOU KNOW,
YOU´RE A COCKY LITTLE KID.

07:52.202 --> 07:54.104
WE OUGHT TO SEE
WHAT YOU CAN DO IN THE RING.

07:54.104 --> 07:56.677
WELL, HE´S ONLY BEEN HITTING
THE BAG FOR A COUPLE WEEKS,

07:56.677 --> 07:58.949
AND HIS MOM DOESN´T EVEN
KNOW THAT HE´S DOING THIS.

07:58.949 --> 08:00.851
THAT´S OKAY.
THEY´LL HAVE ON HEADGEAR.

08:00.851 --> 08:03.884
THEY´LL JUST SPAR A LITTLE.
LET´S GIVE IT A TRY.

08:03.884 --> 08:05.856
ALL RIGHT.

08:09.660 --> 08:12.893
I´M DR. VICTOR PALMERO,

08:12.893 --> 08:14.725
WELTERWEIGHT CHAMPION

08:14.725 --> 08:16.567
OF SEÑORA de la MADRID´S
SCHOOL FOR BOYS

08:16.567 --> 08:21.271
IN 1956, ´57, AND ´59.

08:21.271 --> 08:24.234
CARDIOLOGIST, PUGILIST,

08:24.234 --> 08:27.277
AVAILABLE.

08:27.277 --> 08:28.879
I´M MARRIED.

08:28.879 --> 08:32.242
CONGRATULATIONS.
PERHAPS YOU SHOULD WEAR A RING.

08:34.514 --> 08:37.187
HEY, JOEY,
GIVE MAX HERE A ROUND.

08:46.927 --> 08:48.699
HE´S PRETTY QUICK.

08:48.699 --> 08:51.101
WE HAVE AN OPEN TOURNAMENT
COMING UP IN A COUPLE WEEKS.

08:51.101 --> 08:53.103
YOU MIGHT WANT
TO SIGN HIM UP.

08:55.165 --> 08:56.967
WHOA!

08:56.967 --> 08:59.770
WAY TO GO, DUDE!
THAT´S MY BOY!

08:59.770 --> 09:02.973
I´M SO PROUD OF YOU, MAX!
YOU´RE A REAL FIGHTER, MAN!

09:02.973 --> 09:05.145
DID YOU SEE ME?!
I PUT HIM DOWN!

09:05.145 --> 09:06.977
I´M THE MAN!
OH! OOH!

09:08.248 --> 09:10.250
UH, MAYBE WE SHOULD
PUT A CUP ON HIM

09:10.250 --> 09:12.583
BEFORE HE TAKES
HIS SHOES OFF.

09:19.630 --> 09:21.762
ALL RIGHT, SHE´S NOT HERE.
COME ON.

09:24.134 --> 09:25.736
OKAY, LET´S SEE.

09:25.736 --> 09:27.768
OH, MAN,
IT´S GETTING WORSE.

09:27.768 --> 09:30.941
A BLACK EYE IS SOMETHING
TO BE PROUD OF.

09:30.941 --> 09:32.072
MAX, MY FRIEND,

09:32.072 --> 09:35.606
YOU´RE ON YOUR WAY
TO BECOMING A MAN.

09:35.606 --> 09:37.978
FIRST A BLACK EYE,
THEN FACIAL HAIR,

09:37.978 --> 09:40.781
THEN MAKING LOVE TO A WOMAN
YOU LATER FOUND OUT

09:40.781 --> 09:43.954
YOUR FATHER PAID FOR
WITH A PIG.

09:43.954 --> 09:45.716
VIC!

09:45.716 --> 09:47.988
A PIG WELL SPENT,
IF YOU ASK ME.

09:49.720 --> 09:52.693
WELL, THERE´S NO HIDING
MAX´S BOXING NOW.

09:52.693 --> 09:54.024
YOU´RE GONNA
HAVE TO FACE...

09:54.024 --> 09:57.267
[GASPS] YOUR WIFE!

09:57.267 --> 09:59.129
NO WAY.
WHEN SHE SEES THAT BLACK EYE,

09:59.129 --> 10:01.101
SHE´S NOT GONNA
LET HIM BOX AGAIN.

10:01.101 --> 10:03.273
WELL, LET´S TELL HER
IT HAPPENED IN ART CLASS.

10:03.273 --> 10:05.876
NO. WE´RE NOT
LYING ANYMORE.

10:05.876 --> 10:07.607
THAT´S HOW WE GOT
IN THIS MESS.

10:07.607 --> 10:09.810
LOOK, I´M JUST THINKING
ABOUT COMING CLEAN

10:09.810 --> 10:11.311
AND TELLING HER
THE TRUTH.

10:11.311 --> 10:12.883
[ BANGING ON DOOR ]

10:12.883 --> 10:15.285
I CHANGED MY MIND.
HIDE.

10:15.285 --> 10:17.117
HEY, YOU´RE HOME EARLY!

10:17.117 --> 10:19.920
WOW! LOOK HOW
BEAUTIFUL YOU LOOK!

10:19.920 --> 10:22.793
MAX, GET IN HERE AND HELP
WITH THE GROCERIES!

10:25.295 --> 10:26.957
WHAT´S UP, MOM?

10:28.198 --> 10:30.661
WHY ARE YOU WEARING
CARMEN´S SUNGLASSES?

10:30.661 --> 10:34.064
THAT´S IT!
YOU´RE GROUNDED!

10:34.064 --> 10:35.906
NOW, YOU GO PUT THOSE
BACK IN HER ROOM,

10:35.906 --> 10:37.637
AND YOU THINK
ABOUT WHAT YOU´VE DONE!

10:37.637 --> 10:39.009
BUT ON THE WAY,

10:39.009 --> 10:41.271
DON´T TRIP ON THE END TABLE
IN THE HALLWAY

10:41.271 --> 10:42.943
AND GET A BLACK EYE.

10:42.943 --> 10:45.215
OH, NOW THAT I TOLD HIM,
IT´S PROBABLY GONNA HAPPEN.

10:45.215 --> 10:47.177
THAT´S CRAZY.
HEY, HEY, COME BACK HERE.

10:47.177 --> 10:50.050
TAKE THOSE OFF
BEFORE YOU BREAK THEM.

10:50.050 --> 10:53.083
OH, MY GOD.
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR EYE?

10:53.083 --> 10:57.327
I HIT MY HEAD
ON THE END TABLE IN THE HALL.

10:57.327 --> 11:00.290
WHAT DID I JUST SAY?!

11:00.290 --> 11:02.232
OH, STOP IT.

11:02.232 --> 11:04.895
YOUR MOTHER IS TOO SMART
TO BELIEVE THAT.

11:04.895 --> 11:08.799
THE TRUTH IS...
I HIT HIM.

11:08.799 --> 11:10.941
HE SAID CASTRO
WAS STRONGER THAN SUPERMAN,

11:10.941 --> 11:13.073
AND I LOST MY COOL.

11:14.805 --> 11:17.778
GEORGE, YOUR TURN.

11:19.049 --> 11:21.681
I´M GONNA STICK
WITH FALLING IN THE HALL.

11:23.453 --> 11:25.285
MY SON HAS A BLACK EYE,

11:25.285 --> 11:27.687
AND I WANT TO KNOW
HOW HE GOT IT...

11:27.687 --> 11:29.860
RIGHT NOW.

11:32.122 --> 11:33.894
HE´S BEEN BOXING.

11:33.894 --> 11:35.796
YOU PUT MY LITTLE BOY
IN THE RING

11:35.796 --> 11:37.167
SO OTHER BOYS
COULD HIT HIM?!

11:37.167 --> 11:40.170
LOOK, ANGIE,
IT WASN´T MY IDEA.

11:40.170 --> 11:42.132
LOOK, I´M NOT GONNA
RAT ANYBODY OUT,

11:42.132 --> 11:44.474
BUT THERE´S SOMEBODY
IN THIS KITCHEN THAT SAID

11:44.474 --> 11:47.137
"OYE, CHICO,
I GOT IT -- BOXING."

11:50.010 --> 11:54.214
OYE, CHICO, BENNY --
HE RATTED YOU OUT.

11:59.349 --> 12:00.921
MAX...

12:00.921 --> 12:02.923
GO UPSTAIRS
AND ICE YOUR EYE IN YOUR ROOM.

12:02.923 --> 12:04.955
I NEED TO TALK
TO YOUR IDIOT.

12:06.356 --> 12:09.359
AND YOUR GRANDIDIOTS.

12:09.359 --> 12:10.961
LOOK, ANGIE, RELAX.

12:10.961 --> 12:13.163
THE KIDS WEAR HEADGEAR,
AND THEY FIGHT SHORT ROUNDS.

12:13.163 --> 12:16.006
THEY GET IN THERE --
DING! IT´S OVER.

12:16.006 --> 12:17.968
I MEAN, IT´S SAFE.

12:17.968 --> 12:20.270
YOU KNOW, IN MY 30 YEARS
OF PRACTICING MEDICINE,

12:20.270 --> 12:22.242
I HAVE NEVER ONCE
TREATED A CHILD

12:22.242 --> 12:24.444
FOR SERIOUS INJURY
DUE TO BOXING.

12:24.444 --> 12:26.376
YOU´RE A CARDIOLOGIST.

12:28.278 --> 12:30.450
ONE GOOD THING
ABOUT BEING DIVORCED

12:30.450 --> 12:32.382
IS THAT I CAN DO THIS.

12:35.485 --> 12:39.029
AND I DON´T GIVE A CRAP,
SO I CAN DO THIS.

12:43.763 --> 12:47.798
OKAY.
WHERE SHOULD WE START?

12:47.798 --> 12:49.800
THAT YOU AND MAX
LIED TO ME

12:49.800 --> 12:52.242
OR THAT YOU GOT HIM
DOING SOMETHING DANGEROUS

12:52.242 --> 12:54.404
YOU KNEW I WOULD
NEVER APPROVE OF?

12:54.404 --> 12:56.106
OKAY, LOOK, ANGIE,

12:56.106 --> 12:59.149
MAX HAS BEEN BOXING FOR THE LAST
TWO WEEKS, ALL RIGHT?

12:59.149 --> 13:01.181
HE´S BEEN ABLE
TO FOCUS BETTER IN SCHOOL,

13:01.181 --> 13:04.014
AND HE´S SLEEPING BETTER --
ISN´T THAT WHAT WE WANTED?

13:04.014 --> 13:05.886
BUT AT WHAT PRICE?

13:05.886 --> 13:07.287
I DON´T WANT SOME KID

13:07.287 --> 13:09.990
PUNCHING MY SON IN THE FACE
SO HE CAN SLEEP.

13:09.990 --> 13:12.893
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

13:12.893 --> 13:15.996
HE HIT HIMSELF
TAKING OFF HIS GLOVE.

13:15.996 --> 13:18.568
I BET YOU DIDN´T EVEN
GIVE ART A CHANCE.

13:18.568 --> 13:21.571
AT LEAST WITH ART HE´D BE DOING
SOMETHING MEANINGFUL.

13:21.571 --> 13:23.103
MEANINGFUL?

13:23.103 --> 13:25.075
HEY, DID MICHELANGELO
INVENT A GRILL

13:25.075 --> 13:28.178
THAT KNOCKS THE FAT OUT OF MEAT?
I DON´T THINK SO.

13:30.180 --> 13:32.943
LOOK, ANGIE, YOU´RE THE ONE
THAT´S ALWAYS WORRIED

13:32.943 --> 13:35.185
ABOUT HIS SELF-ESTEEM,
OKAY?

13:35.185 --> 13:37.347
WELL, BOXING IS GIVING IT
BACK TO HIM.

13:37.347 --> 13:40.020
YOU SHOULD SEE HIM.
HE´S LITTLE, HE´S LIKE...

13:42.392 --> 13:45.195
I DIDN´T WANT HIM
GETTING HIS SELF-ESTEEM

13:45.195 --> 13:47.057
FROM HURTING PEOPLE.

13:47.057 --> 13:49.059
Max:
BUT I KNOW I CAN WIN!

13:49.059 --> 13:51.201
HONEY,
COME DOWN HERE.

13:52.863 --> 13:55.035
PLEASE, MOM?
I REALLY LIKE IT.

13:56.466 --> 13:58.568
ANGIE, LOOK,
THERE´S A TOURNAMENT NEXT WEEK.

13:58.568 --> 14:02.112
LET ME SHOW YOU
THAT IT´S SAFE.

14:02.112 --> 14:04.244
HOW CAN YOU SAY NO
TO THIS FACE?

14:04.244 --> 14:07.217
THIS FACE?

14:07.217 --> 14:08.979
PLEASE?

14:08.979 --> 14:12.352
IT´S THE ONLY THING THAT
MAKES ME FORGET ABOUT SCHOOL.

14:15.125 --> 14:17.527
YOU CAN BOX
THIS ONE TIME.

14:17.527 --> 14:19.529
IF I DON´T LIKE IT,
IT´S OVER.

14:19.529 --> 14:22.092
THANKS, MOM.
I´M GONNA GO GET SOME SLEEP.

14:22.092 --> 14:25.565
I GOTTA TRAIN HARD IF I´M GONNA
KICK SOME BUTT NEXT WEEK.

14:28.268 --> 14:30.040
OH, MY NIGHT-LIGHT´S OUT,

14:30.040 --> 14:33.403
SO I´M GONNA LEAVE MY DOOR OPEN
AND THE HALL LIGHT ON.

14:33.403 --> 14:36.646
YOU GOT IT, KILLER.

14:36.646 --> 14:39.209
NO, I´M SERIOUS.
LEAVE IT ON.

14:49.359 --> 14:52.522
YOU OPPONENT IS BIGGER
BUT SLOWER, HMM?

14:52.522 --> 14:55.495
STAY OUT OF HIS REACH,
PICK YOUR SPOTS,

14:55.495 --> 14:57.297
AND REMEMBER THE RHYTHM --

14:57.297 --> 14:58.498
GOOM-GOOM BOM, KA-KING,
GOOM-GOOM.

14:58.498 --> 15:00.200
GOOM-GOOM BOM, KA-KING,
GOOM-GOOM.

15:00.200 --> 15:03.433
OKAY, THAT´D BE GREAT
IF HE WAS FIGHTING
RICKY RICARDO.

15:05.135 --> 15:06.436
JUST REMEMBER,

15:06.436 --> 15:08.508
IT´S NOT IMPORTANT
WHETHER YOU WIN OR LOSE.

15:08.508 --> 15:10.941
WHAT´S IMPORTANT IS THAT
YOUR MOM THINKS YOU´RE OKAY.

15:10.941 --> 15:13.013
SO EVEN IF HE´S
BEATING THE HELL OUT OF YOU,

15:13.013 --> 15:15.045
JUST REMEMBER TO SMILE.

15:15.045 --> 15:17.447
DON´T WORRY, BABY.
HE´S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

15:17.447 --> 15:19.419
HEY, DADDY,
WHAT´S A RING-CARD GIRL?

15:19.419 --> 15:22.352
SOMETHING YOU´LL NEVER BE.

15:22.352 --> 15:24.624
I CAN´T,
BUT THANKS FOR THE SODA.

15:24.624 --> 15:28.058
[ BELL DINGS ]

15:28.058 --> 15:30.200
OKAY.

15:30.200 --> 15:32.462
GENTLEMEN, I WANT A CLEAN,
HARD FIGHT.

15:32.462 --> 15:34.934
OBEY MY INSTRUCTIONS.

15:34.934 --> 15:36.936
TOUCH ´EM UP.

15:40.340 --> 15:42.012
[ BELL DINGS ]

15:42.012 --> 15:43.943
[ CROWD CHEERING ]

15:46.176 --> 15:47.547
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

15:47.547 --> 15:50.350
I´M GONNA HIT YOU EVERY TIME
MY BABY GETS HIT.

15:52.252 --> 15:54.454
YOU LIKE GETTING
HIT IN THE HEAD?

15:57.087 --> 15:58.688
OH, THAT WAS A LOW BLOW.

15:58.688 --> 16:00.660
NO, IT WASN´T!

16:03.733 --> 16:06.236
HE´S GETTING
KILLED IN THERE.

16:06.236 --> 16:08.638
WHY DOES HE KEEP
SMILING AT US?

16:11.501 --> 16:13.143
I´LL TELL YOU
WHAT´S HAPPENING.

16:13.143 --> 16:15.305
HE´S AFRAID TO BE
AGGRESSIVE AND PUNCH BACK

16:15.305 --> 16:17.377
BECAUSE HE KNOWS
YOU WON´T APPROVE.

16:17.377 --> 16:18.678
MAN,
HE´S GONNA GET HURT.

16:20.510 --> 16:24.384
HONEY, IT´S MOMMY!

16:24.384 --> 16:27.587
START PUNCHING, BABY!
I APPROVE!

16:31.391 --> 16:33.163
THAT´S IT, ANGIE!

16:33.163 --> 16:35.525
HE JUST NEEDED TO KNOW
YOU WANTED HIM TO WIN!

16:35.525 --> 16:37.427
YOU GOT IT, MAX!

16:37.427 --> 16:39.429
DADDY WOULD APPROVE
A STRONG RIGHT CROSS!

16:39.429 --> 16:42.001
HE´S OPEN!

16:42.001 --> 16:43.373
MAX!

16:43.373 --> 16:45.175
NOW DADDY WOULD APPROVE
OF YOU GETTING UP.

16:50.610 --> 16:53.143
AND THE CAPITAL
OF CALIFORNIA IS...

16:53.143 --> 16:55.685
SACRAMENTO.
CAN I GO TO BED NOW?

16:55.685 --> 16:57.747
NO, HONEY,
YOU MIGHT HAVE A CONCUSSION.

16:57.747 --> 16:59.449
YOU HAVE TO STAY AWAKE.

16:59.449 --> 17:01.091
IT´S KIND OF FUNNY.

17:01.091 --> 17:03.253
HE STARTED BOXING TO SLEEP,

17:03.253 --> 17:06.556
AND NOW HE CAN´T SLEEP OR ELSE
HE´LL FALL INTO A COMA.

17:08.198 --> 17:11.801
WHOO, ANGIE,
LIFE ON THE BIG BLUE MARBLE.

17:14.164 --> 17:15.665
CAN I SIT DOWN
FOR A WHILE?

17:15.665 --> 17:17.307
ALL RIGHT,
HONEY,

17:17.307 --> 17:19.609
BUT I´M GONNA GET YOU A SODA,
SO YOU STAY AWAKE.

17:19.609 --> 17:21.641
DON´T BE SAD, MAX.

17:21.641 --> 17:23.543
THE FACT THAT YOU
MAY HAVE A CONCUSSION

17:23.543 --> 17:25.645
MEANS THAT YOU PROBABLY
HAVE A BRAIN.

17:27.417 --> 17:30.520
YOU KNOW, PRETTY SOON
I´LL BE ABLE TO BEAT YOU UP.

17:30.520 --> 17:34.384
YEAH, YOU´RE TOUGH,
ALL RIGHT.

17:34.384 --> 17:37.557
♫ LULLABY AND GOOD NIGHT ♫

17:37.557 --> 17:40.390
♫ AND SLIP INTO YOUR COMA ♫

17:40.390 --> 17:42.061
CARMEN...

17:45.395 --> 17:47.197
HOW´S YOUR HEAD FEEL,
HONEY?

17:47.197 --> 17:48.638
IT´LL BE OKAY.

17:48.638 --> 17:51.201
THE NEXT FIGHT
ISN´T FOR A WEEK, ANYWAY.

17:51.201 --> 17:54.504
LOOK, THERE´S NOT GONNA BE
A NEXT FIGHT, MAX.

17:54.504 --> 17:56.776
WHEN I SAW YOU GO DOWN
AND HIT YOUR HEAD LIKE THAT,

17:56.776 --> 17:59.078
I KNEW IT WASN´T WORTH IT,
SO, UH...

17:59.078 --> 18:00.410
BOXING IS OVER.

18:00.410 --> 18:03.113
WHY?!
SO, I GOT HURT.

18:03.113 --> 18:05.355
I COULD GET HURT
SKATEBOARDING,

18:05.355 --> 18:07.117
OR PLAYING SOCCER,

18:07.117 --> 18:09.689
OR PLAYING STEAK-KNIFE DARTS
WITH RICKY.

18:12.122 --> 18:16.566
I HAVE A CONCUSSION.
I DON´T KNOW WHAT I´M SAYING.

18:16.566 --> 18:18.168
THE DIFFERENCE
WITH BOXING

18:18.168 --> 18:21.271
IS SOMEONE IS TRYING
TO HURT YOU.

18:21.271 --> 18:23.133
WHEN YOU GET HURT, MAX,

18:23.133 --> 18:24.834
YOUR MOTHER AND I
WOULD LIKE IT

18:24.834 --> 18:27.777
TO BE MORE
OF A SURPRISE...

18:27.777 --> 18:29.509
WHICH IS GOOD FOR YOU,
TOO,

18:29.509 --> 18:33.183
BECAUSE THE SHOCK
MAKES US CARE MORE.

18:33.183 --> 18:35.685
BUT IT FELT GOOD
WHEN I WAS BOXING.

18:35.685 --> 18:37.347
IT HELPED ME SLEEP.

18:37.347 --> 18:39.689
THEN YOU GOTTA TAKE
THE PRESSURE OFF YOURSELF, MAX.

18:39.689 --> 18:41.751
OKAY, WHAT´S THE WORST THING
THAT COULD HAPPEN

18:41.751 --> 18:43.353
IF YOU FAIL
THE 5th GRADE?

18:43.353 --> 18:45.855
I´LL BE HUMILIATED,
I´LL LOSE ALL MY FRIENDS,

18:45.855 --> 18:48.898
I´LL HAVE TO REDO ALL THE WORK
I HATED DOING THIS YEAR,

18:48.898 --> 18:50.830
AND EVERY DAY
I GO TO CLASS,

18:50.830 --> 18:53.863
I´LL KNOW I´M STUPIDER
THAN EVERYONE ELSE THERE.

18:53.863 --> 18:57.607
WELL, YOU´VE OBVIOUSLY
GIVEN THIS SOME THOUGHT.

19:01.271 --> 19:02.812
OKAY, HERE´S THE DEAL --

19:02.812 --> 19:05.215
UNTIL WE FIND ANOTHER WAY
TO HELP YOU SLEEP,

19:05.215 --> 19:06.776
YOU´RE NOT GOING
THROUGH THIS ALONE.

19:06.776 --> 19:08.618
WE´LL STAY UP WITH YOU.

19:08.618 --> 19:12.182
WE´LL WATCH TV,
AND WE´LL PLAY GAMES.

19:12.182 --> 19:14.384
HEY, AND WE´LL PRANK-CALL
GRANDMA BENNY

19:14.384 --> 19:17.387
LATE AT NIGHT
WHEN SHE´S DRUNK.

19:17.387 --> 19:20.190
"BEN, BEN DOVER?

19:20.190 --> 19:23.233
"THERE´S NO BEN DOVER HERE,
YOU DAMN KIDS.

19:23.233 --> 19:24.594
"IF YOU HAD ANY HUEVOS,

19:24.594 --> 19:26.566
YOU´D COME OVER HERE
AND SAY THAT TO MY GUN."

19:26.566 --> 19:28.668
[ IMITATES CAN OPENING ]

19:31.271 --> 19:34.204
OKAY?

19:34.204 --> 19:35.645
OKAY.

19:39.449 --> 19:41.311
YOU´RE A GOOD DAD.

19:41.311 --> 19:42.682
I JUST THOUGHT
HE´D FEEL GOOD

19:42.682 --> 19:44.814
IF HE KNEW HE WASN´T
GOING THROUGH THIS ALONE.

19:44.814 --> 19:46.586
MAYBE THAT´LL
HELP HIM RELAX

19:46.586 --> 19:49.289
AND HE CAN FINALLY
GET SOME SLEEP...

19:49.289 --> 19:50.620
LIKE HE IS RIGHT NOW.

19:50.620 --> 19:53.693
[ GASPS ] MAX!

19:53.693 --> 19:55.265
UP, UP, UP, UP,
UP, UP, UP.

19:55.265 --> 19:56.696
THE CAPITAL OF WYOMING IS?

19:56.696 --> 19:58.368
I DON´T KNOW.
[ GASPS ]

19:58.368 --> 20:00.370
NO, THAT´S GOOD, ANGIE.
HE REALLY DOESN´T KNOW.

20:06.936 --> 20:09.309
[ SINGING IN SPANISH ]

20:12.812 --> 20:14.614
WHAT?

20:14.614 --> 20:15.715
YOUR SKIN.

20:15.715 --> 20:17.647
I JUST GOT A SPRAY TAN.

20:17.647 --> 20:20.550
I HAVE A HEALTHY GLOW.

20:20.550 --> 20:22.822
YOU LOOK LIKE A HAIRY YAM.

20:32.832 --> 20:35.365
"GET A SPRAY TAN,"
HE SAID.

20:35.365 --> 20:38.338
"CHICKS´LL DIG IT,"
HE SAID.

20:41.641 --> 20:44.414
ERNIE, I´M NOT GOING
TO INSULT YOU.

20:44.414 --> 20:47.547
I JUST HAVE
A MESSAGE FOR YOU.

20:47.547 --> 20:48.948
WILLY WONKA CALLED.

20:48.948 --> 20:50.880
HE WANTS YOU BACK
AT THE FACTORY RIGHT AWAY.

20:50.880 --> 20:52.251
[ LAUGHS ]
